-- Turkey's Garanti secures syndicated loan worth $1.52 bln
-- 
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 07:26AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, April 24 (Reuters) - Turkey's Garanti Bank <GARAN.IS> said on Thursday it secured a syndicated loan in two tranches of $361.4 million and 840.3 million euro ($1.16 billion).

Garanti said in a statement that the cost of syndicated loan was Libor/Euribor + 90 basis points.